44:58.082 --> 44:59.848
There's nothing in my book.

44:59.883 --> 45:01.361
There's... there's
no appointments at all.

45:01.385 --> 45:03.552
I-I was told by Dr.
Masters to clear the whole day.

45:03.587 --> 45:05.787
I spoke on the telephone
with Mrs. Johnson,

45:05.823 --> 45:08.423
and she personally confirmed
these dates with me.

45:08.459 --> 45:10.592
- You're sure, Harriet?
- Of course I'm sure.

45:10.628 --> 45:13.462
And I am sure that you're right,
but Mrs. Johnson didn't tell me.

45:13.497 --> 45:15.230
Can I help with something?

45:15.265 --> 45:16.242
There's been a terrible mix-up.

45:16.266 --> 45:17.699
I'm sorry.

45:17.735 --> 45:20.202
Dr. Masters and Mrs. Johnson
are unreachable today.

45:20.237 --> 45:22.549
The Clavermores have
travelled all the way from Philadelphia.

45:22.573 --> 45:24.473
Clavermore. Of course.

45:24.508 --> 45:26.541
I thought I recognized you.

45:26.577 --> 45:29.544
Didn't Time magazine call you
"The Man Who Fights Fire"?

45:29.580 --> 45:31.279
Mr. Clavermore

45:31.315 --> 45:34.316
runs the largest
asbestos manufacturing plant

45:34.351 --> 45:35.984
I think in North America.

45:36.020 --> 45:37.786
And you must be Mrs. Clavermore.

45:37.821 --> 45:39.421
- I'm Dr. Leveau.
- Well...

45:39.456 --> 45:41.823
I, uh, I work very closely

45:41.859 --> 45:44.326
with both Dr. Masters and Mrs. Johnson.

45:44.361 --> 45:45.927
I can assure you if they were here,

45:45.963 --> 45:48.497
ooh, they'd be mortified
by what's happened.

45:48.532 --> 45:50.899
Happily, I think I can
provide a solution.

45:50.934 --> 45:53.168
Why don't I begin your intake?

45:59.443 --> 46:00.842
Helen?

46:03.781 --> 46:05.647
Hel?

46:05.683 --> 46:07.249
Hey.

46:07.284 --> 46:09.718
Hey. What's wrong?

46:12.856 --> 46:15.590
I did what you said. I...

46:15.626 --> 46:19.094
I told them the truth about...

46:19.129 --> 46:21.663
myself, and...

46:21.699 --> 46:24.466
you, and the baby.

46:24.501 --> 46:26.868
Oh, honey.

46:26.904 --> 46:28.904
What did... what did they say?

46:30.908 --> 46:33.709
Nothing.

46:33.744 --> 46:37.179
They just packed their stuff and left.

46:38.916 --> 46:41.283
I couldn't stop them.

46:41.318 --> 46:43.952
And I've been calling
and calling, and...

46:43.987 --> 46:46.221
it just rings and rings.

46:46.256 --> 46:48.223
They...

46:48.258 --> 46:51.893
they must have pulled
the c-cord out of the w-wall.

46:59.737 --> 47:02.637
I keep thinking about
this dollhouse I used to have

47:02.673 --> 47:04.873
when I was ten.

47:06.910 --> 47:10.512
Three stories. My dad made it.

47:10.547 --> 47:12.180
So many rooms, and...

47:14.184 --> 47:17.519
I'd lie on my stomach with my dolls...

47:17.554 --> 47:19.921
The father and the mother
and the daughter...

47:19.957 --> 47:22.758
And I'd put them in different rooms

47:22.793 --> 47:26.728
and make up things that
they'd say to each other.

47:26.764 --> 47:29.765
And I knew...

47:29.800 --> 47:33.101
that I was never gonna live
in a house like that...

47:34.538 --> 47:37.572
...or have a family like that family.

47:40.611 --> 47:44.045
My family will always be
my own mother and father.

47:45.315 --> 47:48.583
And now... now...

47:48.619 --> 47:50.786
And me.

47:50.821 --> 47:52.854
Me.

47:52.890 --> 47:54.589
And you.

47:54.625 --> 47:56.491
And this baby.

47:57.795 --> 48:00.529
We're your family.

48:00.564 --> 48:04.065
And... and we're gonna
take care of each other.

48:09.173 --> 48:11.072
Yeah.

48:19.683 --> 48:21.316
All rise.

48:29.326 --> 48:31.726
I'm so sorry.

48:31.762 --> 48:34.262
I came straight from the airport.

48:34.298 --> 48:35.764
Good news, Bill.

48:35.799 --> 48:37.732
- I need to talk to you.
- I need to talk to you.

48:37.768 --> 48:40.635
Bob Drag is back on the book.

48:40.671 --> 48:42.437
And I talked to the head of publishing.

48:42.472 --> 48:44.639
They are putting it
on the priority list.

48:46.009 --> 48:48.076
Bailiff, call the jury in, please.

48:48.111 --> 48:49.878
Your Honor...

48:52.349 --> 48:53.949
What is it, Dr. Masters?

48:55.285 --> 48:57.252
I would be willing to discuss a plea

48:57.321 --> 48:59.421
if the prosecution would be willing

48:59.456 --> 49:01.756
to drop the charges
against Mrs. Johnson.

49:03.861 --> 49:06.361
Your Honor, may we discuss this?

49:06.396 --> 49:09.531
My entire negotiation
with Little Brown was based

49:09.566 --> 49:11.600
on the fact that we would
fight these charges

49:11.635 --> 49:13.101
and not plead guilty.

49:13.136 --> 49:15.170
Listen to her, Bill. I still
believe we can win.

49:15.205 --> 49:16.471
Can you give us a moment?

49:18.842 --> 49:20.220
I thought about it, and you were right.

49:20.244 --> 49:21.321
We shouldn't roll the dice.

49:21.345 --> 49:23.879
The book, Bill. Our reputations.

49:23.914 --> 49:25.191
Our reputations are gonna be tainted.

49:25.215 --> 49:26.047
Only if we plead...

49:26.083 --> 49:27.649
Eliot Laskin,

49:27.684 --> 49:29.985
the bellhop from
the Park Chancery Hotel,

49:30.020 --> 49:32.888
is gonna testify.

49:32.923 --> 49:34.901
Keller's made it clear
it's gonna be much worse for you

49:34.925 --> 49:36.892
than it is for me.

49:36.927 --> 49:39.494
Do you really want
all the work you've done,

49:39.529 --> 49:41.963
everything you've achieved,
to be thrown into question?

49:41.999 --> 49:43.732
Now, like you said many times,

49:43.767 --> 49:45.834
the surrogacy program was my idea.

49:45.869 --> 49:47.802
It was my mistake,

49:47.838 --> 49:50.071
and now I'm gonna make it right.

49:50.107 --> 49:51.539
Judge is waiting.

49:57.848 --> 49:59.425
Your Honor, the prosecution will dismiss

49:59.449 --> 50:01.383
the charges against Mrs. Johnson

50:01.418 --> 50:03.919
if Dr. Masters will
agree to plead guilty

50:03.954 --> 50:06.321
to the charge of sexual deviance

50:06.356 --> 50:08.323
and to pay a fine of $500.

50:08.358 --> 50:10.859
Your Honor, I will
plead guilty to the charge.

50:10.894 --> 50:13.061
You're a public figure, Dr. Masters,

50:13.096 --> 50:14.896
so I must point out

50:14.932 --> 50:17.165
that if you accept this plea,

50:17.200 --> 50:19.534
you will be required
to go into that courtroom

50:19.569 --> 50:22.570
and stand in front
of a jury and the press,

50:22.606 --> 50:25.707
and admit to being a sexual deviant.

50:29.546 --> 50:32.614
Sexual deviant.

50:32.649 --> 50:35.216
I'm a scientist who's spent
decades of my life

50:35.252 --> 50:36.418
researching sex.

50:36.453 --> 50:38.954
Even I don't know what that means.

50:38.989 --> 50:41.923
How can something deviate
when there is no norm?

50:43.493 --> 50:47.062
No two humans would...
paint the same painting

50:47.097 --> 50:50.131
or write the same poem
or compose the same opera,

50:50.167 --> 50:51.599
so why would we expect two humans

50:51.635 --> 50:54.569
to express their sexuality
in the same way?

50:54.604 --> 50:56.137
In fact, if there is one thing

50:56.173 --> 50:57.739
the years of research has taught us,

50:57.774 --> 51:00.809
it's that no being's sexual response

51:00.844 --> 51:02.811
is formed on an assembly line.

51:02.846 --> 51:07.482
There is no shape... it must take.

51:07.517 --> 51:09.884
It's as particular

51:09.920 --> 51:13.321
and individualistic as...

51:13.357 --> 51:14.356
a kiss.

51:15.959 --> 51:19.127
And where there is
such infinite variety,

51:19.162 --> 51:21.429
there's no norm.

51:21.465 --> 51:23.298
There's only deviation.

51:24.768 --> 51:26.634
Your honor, I am willing to plead guilty

51:26.670 --> 51:30.672
to sexual deviance,

51:30.707 --> 51:33.842
because I am a sexual deviant,

51:33.877 --> 51:37.479
because we are all sexual deviants.

51:40.650 --> 51:42.751
Go out there and say that to the jury.

51:42.786 --> 51:45.320
We can still win in the
court of public opinion.

51:50.627 --> 51:53.028
The charge is sexual deviance.

51:53.063 --> 51:56.431
How do you plead, sir?

51:56.466 --> 51:58.433
Your honor, I ask you:

51:58.468 --> 52:00.702
how can something deviate
when there is no normal...

52:00.737 --> 52:03.471
I'm gonna stop you
right there, Dr. Masters.

52:03.507 --> 52:06.908
There will be no oration
in my courtroom.

52:08.412 --> 52:10.945
The charge is sexual deviance.

52:10.981 --> 52:12.547
How do you plead?

52:19.523 --> 52:21.056
Guilty.

52:39.209 --> 52:41.876
I thought you were a
man who liked winning.

52:41.912 --> 52:45.547
And yet, your client just
pleaded to sexual deviance.

52:45.582 --> 52:48.016
It was not my idea. Believe me.

52:48.051 --> 52:49.184
It was his entirely.

52:49.219 --> 52:51.152
But why?

52:51.188 --> 52:54.923
I don't understand. It's...
It's not like Bill not to fight.

52:54.958 --> 52:56.691
A witness was gonna come forward.

52:56.726 --> 52:59.994
Things were gonna be said
that would've been bad for Bill,

53:00.030 --> 53:04.032
bad for Virginia, and...

53:04.067 --> 53:06.968
and it would have been entirely
embarrassing to you.

53:09.139 --> 53:10.538
Well,

53:10.574 --> 53:13.575
I do want to put all of that behind me.

53:13.610 --> 53:14.742
So does your husband.

53:14.778 --> 53:17.612
Ex-husband.

53:17.647 --> 53:20.081
Well, that right there...
That's a fresh start.

53:23.153 --> 53:26.087
What is your position on marijuana?

53:26.123 --> 53:27.856
Firm represented LeMar.

53:27.891 --> 53:29.769
They're marijuana activists
based in Washington.

53:29.793 --> 53:31.392
So I say legalize the plant.

53:31.428 --> 53:34.395
And oral sex?

53:36.099 --> 53:37.599
Um, legalize that too.

53:37.634 --> 53:40.135
I'm a huge proponent.
Why are you asking?

53:40.170 --> 53:41.269
What about marriage?

53:41.304 --> 53:42.537
I've had three,

53:42.572 --> 53:44.606
each one more acrimonious than the last.

53:44.641 --> 53:46.741
I don't plan to ever
stand at the altar again.

53:46.776 --> 53:49.043
What about dinner?

53:49.079 --> 53:50.979
My favorite meal of the day.

53:51.014 --> 53:54.082
I mean how would you like
to take me to dinner?

53:55.285 --> 53:56.618
Yes, please.

53:58.155 --> 54:00.088
There are 50 reporters
from every newspaper

54:00.123 --> 54:01.890
and television station in the country.

54:01.925 --> 54:03.625
Now is your chance to do your speech.

54:07.964 --> 54:09.264
- Bill...
- Please, don't.

54:09.299 --> 54:11.065
No. I have to. I have to say thank you

54:11.101 --> 54:12.734
for what you did for me,

54:12.769 --> 54:14.269
for the sacrifice that you made.

54:14.304 --> 54:15.770
- It wasn't a sacrifice.
- Bill...

54:15.805 --> 54:19.474
It wasn't. I did not do this for you

54:19.509 --> 54:21.309
or Libby or anyone else.

54:21.344 --> 54:24.512
I did it for myself.

54:24.548 --> 54:28.483
And I'm sorry if it's
ruined things for the book.

54:28.518 --> 54:31.819
I... I care about the book, of course,

54:31.855 --> 54:33.621
and I care about all of the work,

54:33.657 --> 54:35.657
but I care more about the two of us.

54:39.162 --> 54:42.497
I know that you've
always tried to protect me.

54:42.532 --> 54:46.034
You put my name on the study
so that I would get credit.

54:46.069 --> 54:48.303
And now you sacrifice your reputation

54:48.338 --> 54:50.805
so I don't get the blame.

54:50.840 --> 54:53.107
I know what you did, Bill,

54:53.143 --> 54:55.143
and I know why you did it.

54:59.149 --> 55:04.118
We have been through... a lot,

55:04.154 --> 55:06.354
the two of us.

55:08.258 --> 55:10.792
But now, finally,

55:10.827 --> 55:14.662
we are back where we belong.

55:14.698 --> 55:16.564
Together.

55:16.600 --> 55:18.833
What do you... What
do you mean, "together"?

55:18.868 --> 55:21.202
I mean I...

55:21.238 --> 55:23.671
I want us to be together.

55:46.563 --> 55:48.107
I'm grateful for the opportunity

55:48.131 --> 55:49.897
to speak to you today.

55:51.868 --> 55:56.204
I thought there was nothing
for me in this program,

55:56.239 --> 56:00.742
because, well, I'm not an alcoholic.

56:03.713 --> 56:07.582
But I've come to realize that, uh,

56:07.617 --> 56:11.419
I am an addict... of sorts.

56:14.391 --> 56:15.690
Some of you, all it takes is

56:15.725 --> 56:18.593
a flashing neon sign for cocktails.

56:20.897 --> 56:24.732
For me, well, I can pass
that same sign a thousand times

56:24.768 --> 56:26.100
and never even notice it.

56:26.136 --> 56:29.537
For me, it's...

56:29.572 --> 56:31.439
it's something else.

56:33.576 --> 56:35.009
It's a passing glance.

56:38.448 --> 56:40.815
Fingers brushing against my shoulder.

56:43.753 --> 56:46.487
The linger of perfume when
she's already left the room.

56:48.925 --> 56:50.692
Her hand in mine.

56:53.463 --> 56:56.130
In an instant, I'm r...
I'm ready to give everything up.

56:56.166 --> 56:59.000
I'm... I... I'm
prepared to throw it all away.

56:59.035 --> 57:01.436
My work,

57:01.471 --> 57:03.104
my pride...

57:05.308 --> 57:07.108
...my self-respect.

57:14.451 --> 57:17.185
I'm Bill,

57:17.220 --> 57:19.687
and I'm here to ask for your help.

